### ROS2 Based Robotic Hand Gestures

## File Structure
# build
# install
# log
## src

## Interfaces
# Custom Message  -> Topics
# Custom Service -> Commands
# Custom Actions -> Gestures

# Steps
Create a workspace
Create controller package
Create description package
Create interface package

# Pub/Sub
Topic: /hand/finger_states
QoS queue dept: 10
Runs: Every 0.5 sec with callback
Custom Interface: FingerState.msg (struct format)

# Service/Client
Service: /set_finger
Custom Interface: SetFinger.srv ( Request ... Response )
Responds to Request

# Action
Action: /gesture
Custom Interface: Gesture.action (Goal ... Result ... Feedback )

# Pub/Sub
Visualization Topic: /joint_states
Topic used by Rviz & robot_state_publisher

# start hand controller node
 <!-- ros2 run controller controller -->
# list all topics
ros2 topic echo /hand/finger_statesclear
<!--  -->
# set  a particular finger state via service  call
<!-- ros2 service call /set_finger interfaces/srv/SetFinger "{finger_name: 'index', state: true}" -->


ros2 action send_goal /gesture interfaces/action/Gesture "{gesture_name: 'PEACE'}"

# full system if using only Rviz
conda activate ros_env

colcon build

source install/setup.zsh

ros2 run controller controller

ros2 run controller action_server

ros2 run controller joint_bridge

ros2 launch description rviz.launch.py

ros2 run controller keyboard_control

Configure Rviz: FixedFrame -> base_link 2.0 Add -> RobotModel -> Ok. Description Source->Topic Description Topic -> robot_description


# full system if using only Rviz + Gazebo
conda activate ros_env

colcon build

source install/setup.zsh

ros2 launch description gazebo.launch.py

ros2 control load_controller joint_state_broadcaster
ros2 control load_controller hand_controller

ros2 run controller controller

ros2 run controller action_server

ros2 run controller trajectory_bridge

ros2 run controller keyboard_control


ros2 launch description rviz.launch.py

Configure Rviz: FixedFrame -> base_link 2.0 Add -> RobotModel -> Ok. Description Source->Topic Description Topic -> robot_description





ros2 action send_goal /gesture interfaces/action/Gesture "{gesture_name: 'PEACE'}"
ros2 action send_goal /gesture interfaces/action/Gesture "{gesture_name: 'THUMB_UP'}"
ros2 action send_goal /gesture interfaces/action/Gesture "{gesture_name: 'HI_FIVE'}"
ros2 action send_goal /gesture interfaces/action/Gesture "{gesture_name: 'POINTING'}"
ros2 action send_goal /gesture interfaces/action/Gesture "{gesture_name: 'FUCK_YOU'}"

# Installations
conda install -c robostack -c conda-forge ros-humble-joint-state-publisher-gui

conda install ros-humble-ros2-control ros-humble-ros2-controllers ros-humble-gazebo-ros2-control -c robostack-humble -c conda-forge


ros2 action send_goal /gesture interfaces/action/Gesture "{gesture_name: 'PEACE'}"

# Add below to setup.cfg inside controller
[build_scripts]
executable = /Users/StevenOmole/miniconda3/envs/ros_env/bin/python

# Confirm python version in the build
head -n 1 install/controller/lib/controller/controller

# Then build all packages
colcon build \
    --cmake-args -DPython_EXECUTABLE=$CONDA_PREFIX/bin/python \
    -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE=$CONDA_PREFIX/bin/python


# roughs
ros2 topic info /joint_states --no-daemon